5UFZxI0wlGrURHQ1dq_bjZhlGmYa50ErGX0rXsmJiGBLpNi94hAjwOfeOME3d2yaxxYI-LPuksWxuZsN0cXHb7YN3mrzThFA7hJ66ZcphGa9OmG6fxrCuoWbeeLmIdNYb50LUkOtXqfBtg81tXwfd088M5GegkRZGwt3leMVpxM9ZOzDXTZdd6qwQoxbs1bLXyJt5w-5WGYXsObIsNIk-9UtGIgaslxl99b1FxR67Ksu3U_DDfYRx_hnCO0z-aWMOz4bLU_Ae9F7iILFVJr4TecbluA9LVawoHytrzy6NWMN-mzz6NKpuIAJt40JIH0eRShfJAxDZnqPxPwd-c2_Im6_ea1_LaTYz-UuUOx\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing Class Loading Issues**\\n\\nI need to focus on the Class fallback line, ensuring it has the leading slash for the resource path. Without it, I might end up with a null reference when using `ClassLoader.getResourceAsStream`. I'm noticing that `Class#getResourceAsStream` should return an absolute path, but it seems this resource is located in the test resources path. I also need to create the resource file and check how the metadata agent is recording it.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Determining class name requirements**\\n\\nI'm wondering if the class name should include a dollar sign, like \\\"ObjectHelperTest$PublicConstructible.\\\" It seems like it's important that the name allows for dynamic usage, but I might need to clarify that it shouldn't apply to test class names. I think I'll go ahead and load the class using `loadClass(PublicConstructible.class.getName())`. That feels like the right approach.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering greeting method implementation**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to invoke my greet method. Should I use something like helper.newInstance or create a new Greeter? I'll need a Method object, and using \\\"Greeter.class.getMethod\\\" looks okay. I wonder if there's any potential checkstyle issues, like nested types order? But that seems fine. I should remember that method names should be in lowerCamel case, and I'm checking the line length to keep it under 120 characters. I won't include empty catches!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_KOPkhu4hUSa79AZJdAHoYHW2|fc_0d2e0f4c0f495b72016a284b0133048195930f88526b7fc086", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.camel/camel-core/2.16.2/src/test/java/org_apache_camel/camel_core/ObjectHelperTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_apache_camel.camel_core;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.lang.annotation.ElementType;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Retention;\nimport java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport org.apache.camel.util.ObjectHelper;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ObjectHelperTest {\n    private static final String MANIFEST_RESOURCE = \"META-INF/MANIFEST.MF\";\n    private static final byte[] RESOURCE_BYTES = \"object-helper-resource\".getBytes();\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsClassesWithProvidedClassLoader() {\n        ClassLoader originalClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(null);\n\n            Class<?> loadedClass = ObjectHelper.loadClass(PublicConstructible.class.getName(),\n                    ObjectHelperTest.class.getClassLoader());\n\n            assertThat(loadedClass).isEqualTo(PublicConstructible.class);\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsNewInstancesAndChecksPublicConstructors() {\n        PublicConstructible direct = ObjectHelper.newInstance(PublicConstructible.class);\n        ConstructibleContract cast = ObjectHelper.newInstance(PublicConstructible.class, ConstructibleContract.class);\n\n        assertThat(direct.value()).isEqualTo(\"created\");\n        assertThat(cast.value()).isEqualTo(\"created\");\n        assertThat(ObjectHelper.hasDefaultPublicNoArgConstructor(PublicConstructible.class)).isTrue();\n        assertThat(ObjectHelper.hasDefaultPublicNoArgConstructor(OnlyArgumentConstructor.class)).isFalse();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void findsAnnotatedMethodsThroughClassHierarchy() {\n        List<Method> methods = ObjectHelper.findMethodsWithAnnotation(AnnotatedChild.class, Marker.class, true);\n\n        assertThat(methods).extracting(Method::getName).contains(\"childOperation\", \"parentOperation\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void invokesMethodAndLooksUpConstantFieldValue() throws Exception {\n        Method method = Greeter.class.getMethod(\"greet\", String.class);\n        Object result = ObjectHelper.invokeMethod(method, new Greeter(), \"Camel\");\n\n        assertThat(result).isEqualTo(\"Hello Camel\");\n        assertThat(ObjectHelper.lookupConstantFieldValue(Constants.class, \"ANSWER\")).isEqualTo(\"forty-two\");\n        assertThat(ObjectHelper.lookupConstantFieldValue(Constants.class, \",ANSWER\")).isEqualTo(\"forty-two\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsResourceStreamsFromExplicitContextLibraryAndClassLookups() throws Exception {\n        try (InputStream explicit = ObjectHelper.loadResourceAsStream(\"explicit.txt\", new ResourceClassLoader())) {\n            assertThat(explicit).isNotNull();\n        }\n\n        ClassLoader originalClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new ResourceClassLoader());\n            try (InputStream context = ObjectHelper.loadResourceAsStream(\"context.txt\", null)) {\n                assertThat(context).isNotNull();\n            }\n\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(null);\n        